      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA TERRY (2) rocketed out of the inside draw with a strong early sectional and gave a sight but had to settle for a placing, finishing third (26.44) at Warragul over 460m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Can find winning form. LET'S CAUSE KAOS (4) was a strong winner last time by 5.5 lengths at Geelong in Grade 5 in the quickest time on the program (25.78). Failed to fire only run here. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. One of the prime contenders. SHIV ROY (3) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 6th at Ballarat following on from a third place finish (24.18) at Bendigo the start prior. Expected to give a good account. DREAM ON ALLAN (1) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
